spanGrp.span: They came from a place called Valle de la Estrella.
Jeska jie-wa bete-te m k' kie (_) Valle de la Estrella
From there they walked a lot in the mountain and came out from high above [the mountain].
Jeska jie-wa shk kom' montaa n deu-lo jui wa
Talamanca is located on the other side;
Je wa n esteee Talamanka jatan jamwa
they walked amid bushes and paths, and so they reached Ujarras.
je wa jie-wa shk-g r k'yiga n b triyo n b Jeska jie-wa deu-lo jiska (_) Ujarras
the place was full of trees and bushes;
k' r puro kal-wa jeb k'yiga jeb
there was nothing, no people living here.
ka jir ta ka pe sr kun
There they lived and met others and got horny and got married at once, in Ujarraz.
jeska jie-wa se-n' jeska n jie-wa s'-n kw wa jeska n jie-wa jie-wa jie-wa butan-ka t' jie-wa s' otro-wa ra jeska n jie-wa yabla kon' jiwa jie-wa jula gug-tula-m ji Ujarras
Jeska n (_) ys (r) ys antepasado-wa bete-te Talamanka
My clans name is Julaglwa; there are only two clans in Ujarraz, Julaglwa and Kibglwa;
(_) ys clan r Julablwa y Ujarras sa clan solamente bo-tk' b Julaglwa jm Kibglwa
my family belongs to the Julagwa clan;
the others belong to the Kibglwa clan.
if they had not come here, we would be living in Talamanca, but since they came here we now live here;
jeska n sa/se (_) kennra ka jie-wa bt-pa-ra sa sr-g r Talamanka pero komo jie-wa bete-lo-te jiwa je n wa sa sr-g jiwa
je n wa sa sr-g jiwa
we would not be living in Ujarraz.
kenan ka sa sr kn Ujarras
Thats why our ancestors left us here in this other place to take care of;
je n kweinga sa antepasado-wa t sa jaw'tan ji ji ji k' kajki kwwa kenga knna sa ka r jiwa kun
we live in a different place.
